# MA Activity Log Note Generation

## ICD-10 and goal domains
- ICD-10 codes are stored manually at the student level and mirror SpedForms. They are never inferred from goal domains.
- Goal domains (articulation / language / pragmatics) are inferred separately for display and prompt emphasis only using `inferGoalDomain` from `goalDomainMap.ts`.

## Note body rules
- Never include CPT or ICD-10 codes in generated note text (metadata row carries codes).
- Refer to service by name: "individual/group speech-language treatment".
- Always include session data when provided; if none, state formal data were not collected.
- Always include at least one specific therapy activity (from input or plausible inference).
- Rotate phrasing via `maNoteStyleVariantIndex(studentName, serviceDateYmd)` in `maActivityLogNote.ts`.
- One paragraph, 80–130 words, third person past tense.
- Late entry: prepend exactly `LATE ENTRY — Note written after date of service` (no date), blank line, then paragraph.

## UI (Session Log)
- Metadata row above note: Date | Start | End | Group/Individual | CPT | ICD-10 (red border).
- Note body: plain narrative only via `MaActivityLogNoteDisplay`.

## Post-processing
- Run `postProcessMaActivityLogNote` after AI generation to strip any leaked billing codes.
